@hibikir This generalizes the proposal in https://github.com/linkedin/gobblin/pull/1059/

While making the changes, I also discovered that the socketTimeout was being set to the same value as the fetchTimeout in the old code. This resulted in intermittent failures in Kafka extraction when the amount of data in the source topic is less than the default fetchBytes. This was also commonly reported on the mailing lists by users trying out Kafka ingest locally. 

